HEADWORD: Supra-esophageal
<hw>Su`pra-e`so*phag"e*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Bot. & Zool.)</fld> <def>Situated above, or on the dorsal side of,
the esophagus; <as>as, the <ex>supra-esophageal</ex> ganglion of
Crustacea</as>.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>supra-oesophagal</asp>,
and <asp>supra-oesophageal</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

